[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Overall software testing and validation
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Overall Software Testing and Final Validation phase
for the software element of the railway control and protection system identified
below. It is prepared in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.7 (Overall
software testing / final validation), and collects four output deliverables
from Table A.1:

  24. Overall Software Test Report
  25. Software Validation Report
  26. Tools Validation Report
  27. Release Note

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 (docs 24, 25, 27): BASIC=HR, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.1 (doc 26):           BASIC=--, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.7 (overall analysis and testing techniques):
    Dynamic analysis (A.13):    BASIC=HR, SIL_1=HR, SIL_2=HR, SIL_3=M, SIL_4=M.
    Performance testing (A.18): BASIC=--, SIL_1=HR, SIL_2=HR, SIL_3=M, SIL_4=M.
    Modelling:                  BASIC=--, SIL_1=R,  SIL_2=R,  SIL_3=R, SIL_4=R.

VTR-xxx are executed SW validation test cases; each is the executed counterpart
of a validation test case specification entry in the Software Validation Test
Specification.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: VAL-xxx (requirements), VTR-xxx (validation test cases).
- Duplicate VTR entries for each executed validation test case.
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

