[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Validation test cases executed

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The following VTR-xxx entries are executed validation test cases. Each VTR
entry corresponds to a specification entry in the Software Validation Test
Specification. Duplicate for each executed test case; populate ACTUAL_RESULT
and set VERDICT upon execution.
<<<

[TEST_CASE]
UID: VTR-001
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <Safety function> end-to-end response: nominal activation scenario
TEST_TYPE: Validation
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Complete integrated software loaded on target hardware from baseline <SW-BL-xxx>.
- System in normal operating state; all start-up self-tests passed.
- All external interfaces (IF-EXT-01 through IF-EXT-03) connected to test stimuli.
- No active fault flags; fault log empty at test start.
- Test environment deviations from operational target documented and assessed.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Set system to steady-state operational mode; confirm via status output.
2. Apply nominal activation stimulus for <safety function> at IF-EXT-<n>.
3. Measure elapsed time from stimulus to controlled output change at IF-EXT-<m>.
4. Read system state, output values, and fault log after activation.
5. Remove stimulus; confirm system returns to normal operating state.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- System response time from stimulus to output: < <n> ms (SRS-041).
- Controlled output state achieved as specified in SRS-050.
- No spurious fault log entries generated during nominal activation.
- System returns to normal operating state after stimulus removed: < <n> s.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Response time: <measured_time> ms (limit: <n> ms). WITHIN LIMIT. PASS.
- Output state: <observed_state> (expected: <expected_state>). PASS.
- Fault log entries: 0 spurious entries. PASS.
- Recovery time: <measured_recovery> s (limit: <n> s). WITHIN LIMIT. PASS.
All SRS-041 and SRS-050 criteria met. End-to-end nominal scenario confirmed.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-050
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: VTR-002
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <Safety function> — fault detection and safe state transition
TEST_TYPE: Validation
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- Complete integrated software loaded on target hardware from baseline <SW-BL-xxx>.
- System in normal operating state; all start-up self-tests passed.
- All external interfaces connected; test rig capable of injecting fault
  stimulus on IF-EXT-<n>.
- No active fault flags at test start.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Confirm system in normal operating state; record output state.
2. Inject fault stimulus simulating <failure mode> at IF-EXT-<n>.
3. Measure elapsed time from fault stimulus to safe state application.
4. Read system outputs, fault log, and system state.
5. Attempt normal operation command while fault active; record response.
6. Remove fault stimulus; observe system recovery sequence.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Safe state applied within <n> ms of fault detection (SRS-041).
- Fault code <FC-xx> logged with correct timestamp and category.
- All outputs commanded to safe (de-energised / fail-safe) state.
- Normal operation command rejected while fault active.
- Step 6: system enters recovery sequence; safe state maintained until fault
  cleared and manual reset applied.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Safe state time: <measured_time> ms (limit: <n> ms). WITHIN LIMIT. PASS.
- Fault log: code <FC-xx>, timestamp <HH:MM:SS.mmm>, category <Safety>. PASS.
- All outputs: safe state confirmed on logic analyser channels <n–m>. PASS.
- Normal operation command: rejected (ERR_FAULT_ACTIVE returned). PASS.
- Step 6: system entered recovery sequence; manual reset required before
  resuming operation. Safe state maintained throughout. PASS.
Fault detection, logging, and safe-state transition all confirmed.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-020
  ROLE: Verifies

