[ACTION_ITEM]
UID: PR-VAL-001
STATUS: Closed
TITLE: <Safety function 1>: response time exceeded limit under simultaneous multi-function activation
STATEMENT: >>>
Defect found during VTR-001 extended load scenario. When three safety functions
were activated simultaneously with all communication links at maximum message
rate, the end-to-end response time for <safety function 1> was measured at
<n+x> ms, exceeding the SRS-041 limit of <n> ms by <x> ms.
Impact: timing requirement exceeded; safety impact assessed as Major because
the response time budget does not allow for margin below the hazardous event
reaction time specified in the hazard log.
Fix applied: task scheduling optimised to reduce jitter in the safety-critical
execution path; message processing task yielding policy revised; SAD-021
(scheduling analysis) updated to reflect new task configuration.
Re-test: VTR-001 re-executed after fix under same conditions; PASS.
<<<
OWNER: <Developer Name>
DUE_DATE: <YYYY-MM-DD>
COMMENT: >>>
Fixed in source revision <hash>. Scheduling analysis document re-issued.
WCET measurements (VAL-031) repeated after change; all timing within budget.
Response time confirmed at <measured_final> ms under simultaneous activation.
<<<

