  a) The software as built correctly implements the Software Requirements
     Specification (SRS) in its entirety.
  b) All verification activities have been performed in accordance with the
     Software Quality Assurance Plan (SQAP) and EN 50716:2023.
  c) All lifecycle outputs are complete, consistent, and traceable.
  d) The software is suitable for deployment at the target SIL.

