[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Tools Validation Report

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Tools Validation Report as required by
EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.7 and Table A.1 (document 26). It records the
qualification of all software tools used in the development and verification
lifecycle that may affect the safety of the software product. Tools are
classified as T1, T2, or T3 in accordance with EN 50716:2023 tool
classification criteria:

  T1 — No output used directly or indirectly in software delivered to site;
       no influence on safety function (no qualification required).
  T2 — Output used in the software or verification process, but errors can
       be detected independently (reduced qualification evidence required).
  T3 — Output forms part of the safety case and cannot be fully verified
       independently (full qualification required).
<<<

