[REQUIREMENT]
UID: VAL-120
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Installation and deployment instructions reference
STATEMENT: >>>
Detailed procedures for installing and deploying the software release are
provided in the Software Installation and Deployment Guide referenced below.

Deployment guide reference: <Document ID and revision>

The deployment guide covers:
  a) Pre-installation checks and prerequisites.
  b) Hardware readiness verification (target hardware revision, bootloader
     version, and peripheral configuration).
  c) Software loading procedure (file transfer method, programmer tool,
     version, and configuration).
  d) Post-installation verification: CRC / hash check of loaded binary.
  e) Commissioning tests to be performed on-site before go-live.
  f) Rollback procedure in case of failed installation.
  g) Applicable safety constraints during installation and commissioning.

Safety-critical installation steps:

  Step | Description                                | Verification method
  -----|--------------------------------------------|------------------------------
  <1>  | Verify hardware platform revision = <rev>  | Visual inspection, part number
  <2>  | Load binary <filename.hex> using <tool>    | SHA-256 hash comparison
  <3>  | Execute post-load CRC check                | Automated (tool output)
  <4>  | Verify parameter file version = <v>        | File header check
  <5>  | Execute commissioning test sequence        | Test record sign-off

Installation must not proceed if any of the above checks fail.
Responsible person for installation approval: <Name, Role>
<<<
